node.text: Happy 2nd Birthday baby! I can’t believe you’re already 2 I wish you would slow down a little! Me and your father love you soooo much and are so so proud of you! This past year you took your first steps and are now saying full sentences. What amazes me the most about you is your kind heart and how you say hi to everyone you meet. You also hug and kiss the other kids at daycare when they cry because they miss their parents. How are you so brave already!? I just want you to know that I love you more then myself and am so grateful to be your mother!😭🙏🏽💗

node.text: Loose abdominal skin after growing a human inside of you!? Yeah it happens to EVERYONE! This is currently my biggest physical insecurity that you can’t really see in pictures or when I’m standing. I suffered an umbilical hernia while I was pregnant and still have minor diastasis recti that probably can only be completely corrected through what’s called an umbilicoplasty. AKA belly button surgery. I’ll probably get the procedure done but only after me and Cody are done having babies. I guess I’m just sharing this because I did ALL THE RIGHT THINGS and continued exercising until the day I started having contractions which started on a Cybex Arc by the way!💪🏽😜 Even after doing all the right things I still got an umbilical hernia, some loose skin, diastasis recti, and stretch marks on one of my thighs. That’s life and I’m just happy to be alive and sharing it with my beautiful family!😍🙏🏽💗
